&lt;p&gt;Hill House Home is seeking an experienced Assistant Merchandise Planner to join our New York team, reporting directly to the Director of Merchandise Planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in building pre-season and in-season financial plans by SKU, category, and collection using historical data, sales trends, and strategic growth targets to maximize revenue and margin for omni-channel business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own weekly and monthly reporting process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze business performance (sales, inventory, margin) and present findings to cross-functional stakeholders on both a weekly and ad-hoc basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks and opportunities within owned product categories and communicate findings to Director of Planning and respective cross-functional partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own initial store allocation and in-season replenishment process. Partner with Stores and Store-Operations team to manage inventory capacity within growing Store fleet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory health including sell-through, weeks of supply, and stock coverage. Recommend markdown and pricing strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support new product launches, line reviews, and product lifecycle planning, working alongside Merchant and Design team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion data integrity and SKU-level accuracy across planning systems and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with direct and indirect cross functional partners: merchants, design, production, E-Comm, store operations &amp;amp; marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in monthly/quarterly/annual business reviews and provide insights to support strategic business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in ad-hoc analysis based on business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, Finance, Supply Chain, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3+ years minimum experience in Merchandise Planning or Allocation, preferably within omni-channel consumer goods company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Excel with ability to manipulate large datasets and create dynamic reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities with keen attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills; ability to influence and collaborate across departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoys working in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic, sense of urgency, and commitment to achieving targets and deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized and able to multitask. Effectively manages multiple priorities and adapts quickly to shifting, high-priority demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Takes initiative to provide solutions to improve business processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Naturally inquisitive with strong interest in retail DTC products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
