&lt;p&gt;Hill House Home is seeking a strategic and results-driven Merchandise Planner, to join our New York team to support and expand the planning function across our growing direct-to-consumer business, including eCommerce and retail stores. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Reporting to the Director of Merchandise Planning, the Merchandise Planner will own financial forecasting and in-season strategies, proactively identifying risks and opportunities to maximize revenue and margin, while guiding allocation and inventory decisions to support overall business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the development and execution of pre-season and in-season financial plans by SKU, category, and collection, leveraging historical data, sales trends, and growth targets to maximize revenue and margin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead weekly and monthly reporting, delivering clear, actionable insights to leadership and cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze business performance across sales, inventory, and margin; proactively identify risks and opportunities and present recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Merchandising, Design, Production, E-commerce, and Store Operations to align financial plans with product and channel strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own store allocation strategies and in-season replenishment, ensuring optimal inventory flow and productivity across a growing retail fleet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory health (sell-through, weeks of supply, stock coverage) and recommend pricing and markdown strategies to drive efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product lifecycle management, including new launches, line reviews, and assortment optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and champion data integrity and SKU-level accuracy across planning systems and reporting tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to monthly, quarterly, and annual business reviews, providing insights that inform strategic decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement by identifying opportunities to enhance planning processes, tools, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ad hoc analysis to support evolving business needs and leadership requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4–6+ years of experience in Merchandise Planning or Allocation, preferably within an omni-channel or DTC retail environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills with the ability to analyze large datasets and build dynamic, insightful reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset with the ability to translate data into clear recommendations and business actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident communicator with experience presenting to and influencing cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive and solutions-oriented, with a track record of improving processes and driving results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and relationship-driven, with the ability to work effectively across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Naturally curious, with a strong interest in retail, consumer products, and the DTC landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
